# ===================================================================
# == GIT ATTRIBUTES CONFIGURATION
# ===================================================================

# This file configures Git to manage line endings consistently across different 
# operating systems (Windows, Linux, macOS) to prevent cross-platform build issues.

# 1. Default Rule: Normalize Text Files
# ------------------------------------
# Sets text files to be automatically converted: 
# - text=auto: Git decides if a file is text or binary.
# - eol=lf: All text files are stored in the repository with Unix-style (LF) line endings.
* text=auto eol=lf

# 2. Windows Script Exceptions (CRLF Required)
# -------------------------------------------
# Forces Windows batch scripts to use Windows-style (CRLF) endings, as
# Windows systems often require this format for execution.
*.cmd text eol=crlf

# 3. Unix Executable Scripts (LF Required)
# --------------------------------------
# Explicitly sets the primary executable (Maven Wrapper) to Unix-style (LF)
# to ensure it remains executable on Linux/macOS.
/mvnw text eol=lf